u003E}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs far as I have been able to determine, this draws\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Enothing whatsoever\u003C/strong\u003E; I have several such markers in my save and all of the rings are still visible, but I\u0027ve panned all over the map view hoping to find\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Esome\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0trace of text somewhere at some weird angle\u00A0and\u00A0found nothing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tinkered with this\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Ea lot\u003C/strong\u003E; with and without the canvas components, \u003Cem\u003Emany\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0different values for position and rotation and scale, etc., to no avail. So I don\u0027t need guesses or speculation; I suppose what I\u0027m hoping for is either help with catching a bona fide error in setting up these components, or an example of working code that I can learn from.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, does anyone know how to use UnityEngine.UI.Text in world space?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-09-17T02:34:33Z\u0022 title=\u002209/17/2021 02:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 17, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by HebaruSan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gotmachine","CreatedById":163039,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-23T14:03:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMight not be that, but make sure you set the layer on every gameobject. Also, from memory, you might need layer 5, not 9.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-23T14:33:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223944056\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221616508221\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163039\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gotmachine\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, Gotmachine said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMight not be that, but make sure you set the layer on every gameobject. Also, from memory, you might need layer 5, not 9.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuess what layer these babies are on?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022marker.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002272.78\u0022 height=\u0022238\u0022 width=\u0022327\u0022 src=\u0022https://raw.githubusercontent.com/HebaruSan/PlanningNode/master/screenshots/marker.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the response, but\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223940976\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221615854909\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/16/2021 at 12:35 AM, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tinkered with this\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Ea lot\u003C/strong\u003E; with and without the canvas components, \u003Cem\u003Emany\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0different values for position and rotation and scale, etc., to no avail. So I don\u0027t need guesses or speculation\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mahanako","CreatedById":212725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-04T22:34:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi HebaruSan,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nafter I looked through various projects, I have found this in MOARdV\u0027s Avionics Systems project and it worked in my case drawing text floating in the cockpit. The InternalText class seems to be the KSP equivalent of the UnityEngine.UI.Text. Does this help?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInternalText t;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nt = InternalComponents.Instance.CreateText(\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 font, // eg. \u0022Arial\u0022\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 fontSize, // you need to guess, but in IVA 0.15 gave reasonable size\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 transform, //\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 text, // the actual content string\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 color, // eg. Color.White\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 wrap, // true or false\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 align); // eg. \u0022TopLeft\u0022\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-16T22:05:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to do something similar on the flight scene - just one word....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mahanako","CreatedById":212725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-19T09:15:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI actually did this for the flight scene, more specifically for IVA.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-19T17:33:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224033867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632042935\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mahanako\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, mahanako said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI actually did this for the flight scene, more specifically for IVA.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf your code also works in the map view, I\u0027d be interested to see how you did it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mahanako","CreatedById":212725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-19T20:28:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224033978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632072796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf your code also works in the map view, I\u0027d be interested to see how you did it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll give it a shot and let you know, as soon as\u00A0I find time. But there is this \u0022Internal\u0022 prefix of InternalText and InternalComponents that bothers me a bit. I guess \u0022Internal\u0022 means \u0022inside the cockpit\u0022. I should have noticed this earlier... Maybe there are other components, similar to InternalComponents, that can create text objects as well. Sorry for guessing and\u00A0speculating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}